title: Guest NetIDs and Computer Access: Libraries - Northwestern University
content: A Northwestern NetID is required to access secure online resources. Those without a NetID can obtain a temporary NetID by visiting a library service desk. Guest NetIDs are valid for one day. NOTE: During final exams, guest access to computers may be limited. If you need access to a guest NetID because of special circumstances, please email library@northwestern.eduÂ with your research needs.
